title: Famous birthdays for Oct. 28: Caitlyn Jenner, Nolan Gould
text:
Oct. 28 (UPI) — Those born on this date are under the sign of Scorpio.

They include:

— Dutch scholar Desiderius Erasmus in 1466

— Rifle maker Eliphalet Remington in 1793

— Russian writer Ivan Turgenev in 1818

— Eight-time Academy Award-winning costumer Edith Head in 1897

— Actor Elsa Lanchester in 1902

— English novelist Evelyn Waugh in 1903

— Dr. Jonas Salk, a developer of the polio vaccine, in 1914

— Former baseball Commissioner Bowie Kuhn in 1926

— Country musician Charlie Daniels in 1936 (age 83)

— Basketball Hall of Fame member Lenny Wilkens in 1937 (age 82)

— Actor Jane Alexander in 1939 (age 80)

— Actor Dennis Franz in 1944 (age 75)

— Rock singer Wayne Fontana in 1945 (age 74)

— Singer/actor Telma Hopkins in 1948 (age 71)

— Olympic decathlon champion Caitlyn Jenner in 1949 (age 70)

— Actor Annie Potts in 1952 (age 67)

— Microsoft co-founder Bill Gates in 1955 (age 64)

— Former Iranian President Mahmoud Ahmadinejad in 1956 (age 63)

— Actor Lauren Holly in 1963 (age 56)

— Actor Jami Gertz in 1965 (age 54)

— Comedian Andy Richter in 1966 (age 53)

— Actor Julia Roberts in 1967 (age 52)

— Country singer Brad Paisley in 1972 (age 47)

— Actor Joaquin Phoenix in 1974 (age 45)

— Actor Gwendoline Christie in 1978 (age 41)

— Actor Matt Smith in 1982 (age 37)

— Actor Finn Wittrock in 1984 (age 35)

— Actor Troian Bellisario in 1985 (age 34)

— Singer Frank Ocean in 1987 (age 32)

— Actor Devon Murray in 1988 (age 31)

— Actor Nolan Gould in 1998 (age 21)
